# T2S - Text to SQL CLI

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/t2s-cli.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/t2s-cli)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Python 3.8+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.8+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)

A powerful terminal-based Text-to-SQL converter that uses AI models to transform natural language queries into SQL statements and execute them against your local databases.

**Created by Lakshman Turlapati**

## Features

🚀 **AI-Powered SQL Generation**
- Support for multiple state-of-the-art models (Gemma 3, Llama 3, SmallLM, Defog SQLCoder)
- Intelligent schema analysis and compression
- Automatic SQL query validation and correction

🎯 **Smart Database Integration**
- Auto-detection of local databases (SQLite, PostgreSQL, MySQL)
- Intelligent schema selection based on query context
- Real-time query execution and results display

🎨 **Beautiful Terminal Interface**
- ASCII art branding
- Rich formatting and syntax highlighting
- Interactive configuration menu
- Progress bars and status indicators

🔧 **Model Management**
- Automatic model downloading from HuggingFace
- Optional HuggingFace OAuth integration
- Local model storage and management
- Easy model switching and deletion

🌍 **Cross-Platform Support**
- Compatible with macOS, Windows, and Linux
- Support for both ARM and x86 architectures
- Auto-detection of system capabilities

## Installation

### From PyPI (Recommended)

```bash
pip install t2s-cli
```

### From Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/lakshmanturlapati/t2s-cli.git
cd t2s-cli
pip install -e .
```

## Quick Start

1. **Launch T2S**
   ```bash
   t2s
   ```

2. **First-time Setup**
   - Configure your AI model preferences
   - Set up database connections
   - Download your preferred AI model

3. **Start Querying**
   ```bash
   t2s query "Show me all users who registered last month"
   ```

## Usage

### Interactive Mode

```bash
t2s
```

Launch the interactive terminal interface with full features.

### Direct Query Mode

```bash
t2s query "Find all products with price greater than 100"
```

### Configuration

```bash
t2s config
```

Access the configuration menu to:
- Select and download AI models
- Configure database connections
- Manage HuggingFace authentication
- Delete unused models

### Help

```bash
t2s --help
```

## Supported AI Models

- **Gemma 3 (4B)** - Fast and efficient for simple queries
- **Gemma 3 (12B)** - More accurate for complex queries
- **Llama 3 (4B)** - Balanced performance and accuracy
- **SmallLM (1.7B)** - Lightweight option for basic queries
- **Defog SQLCoder (7B)** - Specialized for SQL generation

## Supported Databases

- SQLite
- PostgreSQL
- MySQL
- More coming soon!

## Examples

### Basic Query
```
Input: "Show me all customers from New York"
Generated SQL: SELECT * FROM customers WHERE city = 'New York';
```

### Complex Query
```
Input: "Find the top 5 products by revenue last quarter"
Generated SQL: 
SELECT p.name, SUM(oi.quantity * oi.price) as revenue
FROM products p
JOIN order_items oi ON p.id = oi.product_id
JOIN orders o ON oi.order_id = o.id
WHERE o.created_at >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 3 MONTH)
GROUP BY p.id, p.name
ORDER BY revenue DESC
LIMIT 5;
```

